<paragraph blockId="17.[533,1054,267,329]" box="[634,953,302,329]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<figureCitation box="[634,739,302,329]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStartId-0="4.[189,232,1813,1839]" captionStartId-1="5.[189,232,1713,1739]" captionTargetBox-0="[306,1276,844,1746]" captionTargetBox-1="[206,1387,908,1645]" captionTargetId-0="figure@4.[281,1305,819,1760]" captionTargetId-1="figure@5.[189,1400,879,1658]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionText-0="Fig. 1. Bayesian phylogeny of 19 species from the ‘D. montium species group’ Da Lage, 2007 inferred from complete mitochondrial genomes. Nodes supported by 100% posterior probability (pp) are not labeled, those with pp&gt; 90% or 60% are labeled with gray and white circles, respectively. Species belonging to the ‘D. bocqueti species complex’ and the ‘D. bakoue species complex’ are highlighted in orange and green, respectively. ‘K’ and ‘B’ refer to the strains of D. aff tsacasi Bock &amp; Wheeler, 1972 from Kenya and Bioko Island, respectively." captionText-1="Fig. 2. Comparison of Bayesian phylogenies of the ‘D. seguyi species subgroup’ Yassin, 2018 inferred from mitochondrial COI (left) and nuclear Amyrel (right) genes. Nodes supported by&gt;95% posterior probability (pp) are labeled with black circles. An asterisk refers to species sequenced here, whereas two asterisks refer to the sequence of D. vulcana Graber, 1957 of Da Lage et al. (2007), which turned out to belong to D. seguyi Smart, 1945 from Kenya (see the text). Note the discrepancy in position of different geographical strains of D. bakoue Tsacas &amp; Lachaise, 1974 (in red) between the two genes. Species belonging to ‘D. bocqueti species complex’ Tsacas &amp; Lachaise, 1974, ‘D. bakoue species complex’ Rafael, 1984, ‘D. nikananu species complex’ Tsacas &amp; Chassagnard, 1992, and ‘D. megapyga species complex’ Lachaise &amp; Tsacas, 2001 are highlighted in orange, green, yellow and red, respectively." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3251571/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3251573/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[751,787,303,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1921,1947]" captionTargetBox="[201,1393,1370,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,1344,1865]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Photomicrographs of male periphallic organs. A. D. seguyi Smart, 1945 (MNHN). B. D. aff. tsacasi Bock &amp; Wheeler, 1972 (MNHN). C. D. mylenae David &amp; Yassin sp. nov. (MNHN). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251575/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">3C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[800,813,303,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[215,1384,1143,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1398,1108,1904]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. Adult habitus. A–B. D. vulcana Graber, 1957 (MNHN). A. ♂. B. ♀. C–D. D. mylenae David &amp; Yassin sp. nov. (MNHN). C. ♂. D. ♀. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251585/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">8</figureCitation>
A–D, 9A–F
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,310,368,394]" box="[189,310,368,394]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,368,394]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,368,394]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1399,414,652]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Male abdominal tergites yellow, T2–T4 with broad brown or black stripes, T5 and T6 with a thin black stripe expanding on the middle and fainting towards the margin (
<figureCitation box="[936,1029,450,476]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[215,1384,1143,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1398,1108,1904]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. Adult habitus. A–B. D. vulcana Graber, 1957 (MNHN). A. ♂. B. ♀. C–D. D. mylenae David &amp; Yassin sp. nov. (MNHN). C. ♂. D. ♀. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251585/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
); cercal ventral lobe (secondary clasper) partially separated from cerci with two or three very large curved black medial teeth on the internal margin; surstylus with a lateral row of strong, short prensisetae on the outer and inner margins (no medial prensisetae), the innermost one significantly long; hypandrial median process tapering (
<figureCitation box="[198,294,590,617]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1921,1947]" captionTargetBox="[201,1393,1370,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,1344,1865]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Photomicrographs of male periphallic organs. A. D. seguyi Smart, 1945 (MNHN). B. D. aff. tsacasi Bock &amp; Wheeler, 1972 (MNHN). C. D. mylenae David &amp; Yassin sp. nov. (MNHN). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251575/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); aedeagus hirsute with cuticular scales; inner paraphyses as long as aedeagus, with finely serrated margins (
<figureCitation box="[399,468,626,652]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[225,1374,307,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[189,1398,265,1858]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 9. Terminalia of the ‘D. vulcana species complex’. A, C, E. D. vulcana Graber, 1957 (MNHN). A, C. ♂. E. ♀. B, D, F. D. mylenae David &amp; Yassin sp. nov. (MNHN). B, D. ♂. F. ♀. Scale bars: A–B = 50 µm; D–F = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251587/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
A–D). Female abdominal tergites darker than male’s (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1193,626,652]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[215,1384,1143,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1398,1108,1904]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. Adult habitus. A–B. D. vulcana Graber, 1957 (MNHN). A. ♂. B. ♀. C–D. D. mylenae David &amp; Yassin sp. nov. (MNHN). C. ♂. D. ♀. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251585/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
